{
  "page": "Jhattar",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>A <i><b>jhattar</b></i> is the \"<i><a href=\"/index.php/Jhat\" title=\"Jhat\">jhat</a></i> of <i>jhats</i>\" or war leader of the whole people among the <a href=\"/index.php/Jogos_Nhai\" title=\"Jogos Nhai\">Jogos Nhai</a>. By tradition, they own a drinking cup made from the gilded skull of <a href=\"/index.php/Lo_Bu\" title=\"Lo Bu\">Lo Bu</a>, the forty-third and last <a href=\"/index.php/Scarlet_emperors\" title=\"Scarlet emperors\">scarlet</a> <a href=\"/index.php/God-Emperor\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"God-Emperor\">emperor</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Golden_Empire_of_Yi_Ti\" title=\"Golden Empire of Yi Ti\">Golden Empire of Yi Ti</a>. Dozens of <i>jhattars</i> have led the Jogos Nhai against the city of <a href=\"/index.php/Kayakayanaya\" title=\"Kayakayanaya\">Kayakayanaya</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_bones_and_beyond:_the_plains_of_the_jogos_nhai.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_bones_and_beyond:_the_plains_of_the_jogos_nhai.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Known_Jhattars\">Known <i>Jhattars</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Jhattar&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Known Jhattars\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Zhea\" title=\"Zhea\">Zhea</a>, known as Zhea the Barren, Zhea Zorseface, and Zhea the Cruel, the first <i>jhattar</i>. Led the war against <a href=\"/index.php/God-Emperor\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"God-Emperor\">God-Emperor</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Lo_Bu\" title=\"Lo Bu\">Lo Bu</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Gharak\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gharak\">Gharak</a>, known as Gharak Squint-Eye, who according to legend slew the last of the <a href=\"/index.php/Jhogwin\" title=\"Jhogwin\">Jhogwin</a> at the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_in_the_Howling_Hills\" title=\"Battle in the Howling Hills\">Battle in the Howling Hills</a>.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Jhattar&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_bones_and_beyond:_the_plains_of_the_jogos_nhai.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_bones_and_beyond:_the_plains_of_the_jogos_nhai.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Bones and Beyond: The Plains of the Jogos Nhai.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"navbox\" style=\"border-spacing:0;;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"padding:2px;\"><table cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"nowraplinks hlist collapsible autocollapse navbox-inner\" style=\"border-spacing:0;background:transparent;width:100%;color:inherit;;;\"><tbody><tr><th scope=\"col\" style=\";\" class=\"navbox-title\" colspan=\"2\"><div class=\"plainlinks hlist\" style=\"display:block;float:left;font-weight:normal;font-size:88%;padding-top:3px;text-align:left;width:6.8em;\"><ul><li class=\"nv-view\"><a href=\"/index.php/Template:Rulers\" title=\"Template:Rulers\"><span title=\"View this template\" style=\";;background:none transparent;border:none;\">v</span></a></li><li class=\"nv-talk\"><a href=\"/index.p